  "body": "The below fails to find validators because it can't read the keystores (my fault, I needed to use `sudo -u teku`). However it should have failed more gracefully than with a NPE.\r\n\r\n```\r\n$ ./build/install/teku/bin/teku voluntary-exit --config-file tmp/teku.yaml --epoch 24500\r\nLoading configuration...\r\nExits are going to be generated for validators:\r\n\r\n\r\nThese validators won't be able to be re-activated, and withdrawals aren't likely to be possible until Phase 2 of eth2 Mainnet.\r\nAre you sure you wish to continue (yes/no)?\r\nyes\r\njava.lang.NullPointerException\r\n        at tech.pegasys.teku.cli.subcommand.VoluntaryExitCommand.submitExitForValidator(VoluntaryExitCommand.java:139)\r\n        at java.base/java.util.HashMap.forEach(HashMap.java:1338)\r\n        at tech.pegasys.teku.cli.subcommand.VoluntaryExitCommand.run(VoluntaryExitCommand.java:89)\r\n        at picocli.CommandLine.executeUserObject(CommandLine.java:1919)\r\n        at picocli.CommandLine.access$1100(CommandLine.java:145)\r\n        at picocli.CommandLine$RunLast.executeUserObjectOfLastSubcommandWithSameParent(CommandLine.java:2332)\r\n        at picocli.CommandLine$RunLast.handle(CommandLine.java:2326)\r\n        at picocli.CommandLine$RunLast.handle(CommandLine.java:2291)\r\n        at picocli.CommandLine$AbstractParseResultHandler.execute(CommandLine.java:2159)\r\n        at picocli.CommandLine.execute(CommandLine.java:2058)\r\n        at tech.pegasys.teku.cli.BeaconNodeCommand.parse(BeaconNodeCommand.java:229)\r\n        at tech.pegasys.teku.Teku.main(Teku.java:32)\r\n```\r\n\r\nReproducible test case:\r\n```\r\n$ ./build/install/teku/bin/teku voluntary-exit --epoch 24500\r\nLoading configuration...\r\nExits are going to be generated for validators:\r\n\r\n\r\nThese validators won't be able to be re-activated, and withdrawals aren't likely to be possible until Phase 2 of eth2 Mainnet.\r\nAre you sure you wish to continue (yes/no)?\r\nyes\r\njava.lang.NullPointerException\r\n        at tech.pegasys.teku.cli.subcommand.VoluntaryExitCommand.submitExitForValidator(VoluntaryExitCommand.java:139)\r\n```\r\n\r\nInstead of proceeding, the command should detect that no keystores were loaded and print a helpful error message.",
